Entries.default: "Why in the blackest Hel are you clomping around so loud? Howbeit! You're not allowed up here, you no good fuddlers."
"Step. Back. I will not warn you again, you boosy bastard."

"You're thrice damned now. Hope you like hanging by your toes."

Raising a horn to her lips, she takes a deep breath.
"Draw cutlasses! Aim cannons! All pirates to arms!"
[Attack] "I go where I please."
[Back away with your hands up.] "No need to get testy."
"You sodden wharf rat! I'll put a ball between your eyes to stop your scurrying!"
"No, I best escort you back. Follow me if you want to keep living. Try to sneak past if you want to die."
"You got a problem with drunks?"
"Just got no patience for them, the bilge-lickers. It's rot enough I'm posted next to the forge. Having to listen to that hammer striking nonstop, all day long."
"Enough gabbling. The ramparts are off-limits to anyone but Benweth's crew. Run off, or I'll run you through."
"For the last time, pipe down, the lot of you!"
"Flog off, we ain't hurting nothing."
"I ought to throw you in irons! Think I can't? Think Ben would care what happens to you?"
"Ondra drown those no-good drunkards and their raucous louting!"
Shrugging, the pirates flanking the guard amble away.
"I don't think Aeldys would like it none, no."
"Aeldys ain't here, is she? So shut up or I'll drown you in your own grog."
"Add on those howling guzzlers at the bottom of the stairs, and you get the picture."
"Heard you got a deal going with Ben. Come on through then. Run of the fort's yours."
